ists%20who%20have%20worked%20in%20this%20field%20went%20clearly%20and%20unmistakably%20on%20record%20as%20to%20their%20opposition%20on%20moral%20grounds%20to%20the%20use%20of%20these%20bombs%20in%20the%20present%20phase%20of%20the%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Szilard%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dannen.com%2Fdecision%2F45-07-04.html%5C%22%3Epetition's%20cover%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20didn't%20include%20names%20from%20the%20Los%20Alamos%2C%20New%20Mexico%20scientists%20because%20they%20weren't%20given%20the%20chance%20to%20sign%2C%20Edward%20Teller%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20Project's%20scientists%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fvoices%2Foral-histories%2Fedward-tellers-interview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elater%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJ.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%2C%20director%20of%20Los%20Alamos%20Laboratory%2C%20persuaded%20Teller%20not%20to%20distribute%20the%20petition.%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer%20talked%20me%20out%20of%20it%2C%20saying%20that%20we%20as%20scientists%20have%20no%20business%20to%20meddle%20in%20political%20pressure%20of%20that%20kind%2C%26quot%3B%20Teller%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Teller%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FLos_Alamos_Science%2FRNSyoG42FOYC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%2522the%2Bthings%2Bwe%2Bare%2Bworking%2Bon%2Bare%2Bso%2Bterrible%2Bthat%2Bno%2Bamount%2Bof%2Bprotesting%2Bor%2Bfiddling%2522%26pg%3DPA193%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20to%20Szilard%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20things%20we%20are%20working%20on%20are%20so%20terrible%20that%20no%20amount%20of%20protesting%20or%20fiddling%20with%20politics%20will%20save%20our%20souls.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETruman%20didn't%20actually%20see%20the%20petition%20before%20he%20ordered%20the%20bo