ared)%2C%2078.84%25%20of%20panchayat%20samiti%20seats%20(6%2C716%20of%208%2C518%20seats%20and%201%2C210%20results%20were%20yet%20to%20be%20officially%20declared)%2C%20and%2065.69%25%20of%20gram%20panchayat%20seats%20(35%2C606%20of%2054%2C195%20and%20another%209%2C027%20results%20were%20yet%20to%20be%20officially%20declared).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20strikingly%20high%20share%20of%20seats%20compared%20to%20the%20vote%20share%20is%20that%20the%20opposition%20votes%20got%20divided%2C%20often%20sharply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%2C%20they%20were%20split%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Left%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20with%20the%20Congress%20as%20another%20factor.%20This%20is%20the%20biggest%20cause%20of%20concern%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20as%20its%20impressive%20performance%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20and%20emergence%20as%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%20were%20made%20possible%20due%20to%20the%20consolidation%20of%20opposition%20votes%20in%20its%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20combined%20vote%20share%20of%20the%20Left%2C%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20Indian%20Secular%20Front%20(ISF)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20stood%20at%20a%20meagre%2010%25%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%20%E2%80%93%20has%20crossed%20the%2020%25%20mark%20in%20the%20panchayat%20election.%20The%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20share%20was%20down%20to%2023%25%2C%20from%2040%25%20in%202019%20and%2038%25%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20many%20political%20observers%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20and%20seat%20share%20both%20appear%20inflated%20due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbengal-panchayat-election-violence-2%5C%22%3Escale%20of%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20alleged%20electoral%20malpractices%20that%20marred%20the%20rural%20polls%20%E2%80%93%20over%2040%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20pre-poll%2C%20poll-day%20and%20post-poll%20violence.%20They%20expect%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20to%20go%20down%20by%20a%20few%20percentage%20points%20when%20the%20elections%20are%20held%20under%20the%20watch%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20in%20multiple%20phases%20and%20with%20greater%20security%20cover.%20The%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20and%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%20stood%20at%2043%25%20and%2048%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20possibility%20does%20not%20provide%20the%20BJP%20with%20any%20relief%20because%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20coming%20uncomfortably%20close%20to%20its%20own%20%E2%80%93%20creating%20a%20sharp%20divide%20in%20opposition%20votes.%20This%20rise%20in%20Left%20vote%20share%20is%20also%20consistent%20with%20the%20trends%20of%20the%20post-2021%20assembly%20election%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnot-just-tmc-the-left-too-can-hurt-bjp-in-the-bengal-civic-polls%5C%22%3Ebypolls%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Ftmc-supremacy-to-continue-as-bengal-re-enters-a-phase-of-divided-opposition-news-191991%5C%22%3E2022%20civic%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20both%20cases%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENumber%20game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20stood%20at%2022.9%25%2C%20winning%2018.24%25%20of%20gram%20panchayat%20seats%2C%2012.25%25%20of%20panchayat%20samiti%20seats%20and%2026%20zilla%20parishad%20seats.%20The%20Left%2C%20with%20a%2013.2%25%20vote%20share%2C%20won%205.8%25%20of%20gram%20panchayat%20seats%2C%202.3%25%20of%20panchayat%20samiti%20seats%20and%202%20zilla%20parishad%20seats.%20The%20Congress%2C%20with%20a%206.42%25%20vote%20share%2C%20won%204.82%25%20of%20gram%20panchayat%20seats%2C%203.2%25%20of%20panchayat%20samiti%20seats%20and%2012%20zilla%20parishad%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20the%20Congress%20won%20more%20seats%20than%20the%20Left%20despite%20a%20smaller%20vote%20share%20is%20that%20their%20strength%20is%20concentrated%20mostly%20in%20the%20districts%20of%20Malda%20and%20Murshidabad%2C%20where%20their%20share%20of%20votes%20was%20significantly%20high%2C%20whereas%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20spread%20across%20several%20districts%2C%20mostly%20in%20central%20and%20south%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13152324%2FScreenshot-2023-07-13-at-3.22.09.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13152324%2FScreenshot-2023-07-13-at-3.22.09.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13152324%2FScreenshot-2023-07-13-at-3.22.09-300x148.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13152324%2FScreenshot-2023-07-13-at-3.22.09-1024x506.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663004%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22593%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFlags%20of%20TMC%20and%20CPI(M)%20in%20rural%20Bengal%20on%20panchayat%20poll%20day.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20several%20central%20and%20south%20Bengal%20districts%20%E2%80%93%20the%20region%20with%2034%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%2042%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20stood%20above%2016%25.%20This%20cost%20the%20BJP%20dozens%20of%20Zilla%20Parishad%20seats%2C%20while%20the%20CPI(M)%2C%20too%2C%20lost%20several%20seats%20due%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share.%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20TMC%20benefitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20r