eg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663006%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22607%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPeople%20queue%20to%20vote%20in%20Junglemahal%2C%20Bengal.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20block-wise%20results%20of%20ZP%20seats%20(blocks%20usually%20have%202-3%20ZP%20seats)%2C%20in%20Jangipara%20and%20Haripal%20of%20Hooghly%20district%20where%20the%20TMC%20was%20way%20ahead%20of%20both%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20and%20the%20Left%20stood%20nearly%20neck%20and%20neck%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Jangipara%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%2027932%20was%20slightly%20above%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%2026%2C480%20and%20in%20Haripal%20BJP%E2%80%99s%2037%2C509%20was%20a%20little%20above%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%2030%2C478.%20Jangipara%20falls%20in%20Serampore%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Haripal%20in%20Arambag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ZP-wise%20result%20of%20Gangajalghati%20block%20in%20Bankura%20district%20shows%20the%20following%20vote%20share%20%E2%80%93%2053%2C021%20(46%25)%2C%20BJP%2043%2C145%20(37.41%25)%2C%20Left%20%E2%80%93%2017%2C187%2C%20(14.9)%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%201%2C969.%20In%20Indpur%20block%20of%20the%20same%20district%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20votes%20stood%20at%2044%2C134%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20at%2030%2C446%20and%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20at%2020%2C012.%20In%20Hirabandh%20and%20Khatra%20blocks%2C%20the%20Left%20and%20the%20BJP%20played%20spoilsport%20for%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20big%20picture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20get%20the%20Lok%20Sabha-wise%20picture%20of%20local%20body%20election%20results%20is%20to%20add%20the%20figures%20for%20the%20Zilla%20parishad%20seats%2C%20the%20highest%20tier%20of%20the%20panchayat%20system%2C%20as%20the%20ZP%20seats%20are%20considered%20to%20reflect%20the%20closest%20trend%20to%20assembly%20election%20voting%20patterns.%20Each%20assembly%20is%20made%20of%20two%20to%20four%20ZP%20seats%20and%20sometimes%20urban%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELok%20Sabha-specific%20results%20of%20the%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20civic%20polls%20and%20the%20recent%20panchayat%20elections%20show%20that%20in%20Hooghly%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20which%20the%20BJP%20won%20in%202019%20with%20a%20margin%20of%2073%2C000%20votes%2C%20the%20Left%20and%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20cumulative%20votes%20secured%20in%20urban%20and%20rural%20elections%20stand%20above%20what%20the%20BJP%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-bengals-panchayat-polls-will-be-different-this-year%5C%22%3EWhy%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20Panchayat%20Polls%20Will%20Be%20Different%20This%20Year%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHooghly%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20made%20of%2021%20ZP%20seats%20and%20three%20urban%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20Chandannagar%20municipal%20corporation%2C%20Hooghly-Chinsurah%20municipality%20and%20Bansberia%20municipality.%20The%20results%20of%20these%2021%20zilla%20parishad%20seats%20show%20the%20TMC%20has%20got%205%2C93%2C217%20votes%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%20has%20got%20271411%20votes%20and%20the%20Left%20secured%202%2C18%2C122.%20In%20the%202022%20urban%20elections%2C%20the%20TMC%20secured%201%2C40%2C009%20votes%2C%20the%20Left%20got%2077%2C003%20votes%20and%20the%20BJP%20polled%2031%2C568%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20vote%20stands%20at%207%2C33%2C226%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20at%203%2C02%2C979%20and%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20at%202%2C95%2C125.%20However%2C%20the%20Congress%20polled%20over%20another%2025%2C000%20votes%20in%20these%20polls.%20The%20Left-Congress%20combined%20votes%20are%20thus%20above%20what%20the%20BJP%20polled%20in%20the%20local%20elections.%20Even%20though%20the%20Left%20and%20the%20Congress%20mostly%20contested%20separately%20in%20the%20local%20body%20election%2C%20they%20are%20going%20together%20in%20most%20assembly%20or%20parliamentary%20elections%20and%20by-elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Left-Congress%20votes%20reflect%20a%20significant%20improvement%20in%20their%20performances%2C%20as%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20they%20polled%201%2C46%2C962%20votes%20fighting%20separately%20and%20in%202021%20secured%201%2C71%2C100%20votes%20in%20the%20seven%20seats%20that%20make%20up%20Hooghly%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20fighting%20in%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%20in%20Malda%20Uttar%20Lok%20Sabha%20of%20northern%20Bengal%2C%20which%20the%20BJP%20won%20in%202019%20with%20a%20margin%20of%2084%2C288%20votes%2C%20the%20local%20body%20election%20statistics%20put%20the%20BJP%20at%20the%20third%20position.%20Habibpur%2C%20Bamangola%2C%20Gazole%2C%20Chanchal%20I%20and%20II%2C%20Harishchandrapur%20I%20and%20II%20and%20Ratua%20I%20and%20II%20community%20development%20blocks%20and%20Old%20Malda%20municipality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F22123105%2F20210415_132321.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F22123105%2F20210415_132321.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F22123105%2F20210415_132321-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F22123105%2F20210415_132321-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-524129%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EElection%20graffiti%20at%20a%20village%20in%20Gazole%2C%20Malda.%20Photo%3A%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20zilla%20parishad%20seats%20that%20make%20up%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Old%20Maldah%20municipality%2C%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20votes%20stand%20at%204%2C59%2C536%2C%20the%20Left-Congress%20combined%20vote%20at%203%2C20%2C402%20and%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20at%20233%2C121.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20got%205%2C09%2C524%20votes%2C%20against%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%204%2C25%2C236%2C%20while%20the%20Left-Congress%20cumulative%20votes%20stood%20at%203%2C55%2C671.%20In%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%2C%20the%20TMC%2C%20BJP%20and%20Left-Congress%20alliance%E2%80%99%20votes%20stood%20at%207%2C46%2C681%20votes%2C%204%2C71%2C042%20votes%20and%201%2C51%2C060%20votes%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bishnupur%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%20Bankura%20district%20of%20southwestern%20Bengal%2C%20the%20Zilla%20parishad%20and%20civic%20body%20election%20results%20put%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20votes%20at%207%2C90%2C166%20votes%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20stood%20at%204%2C11%2C841%20and%20the%20Left-Congress%20combine%E2%80%99s%20at%202%2C32%2C760.%20Over%202%20lakh%20of%20this%20is%20the%20Left%E2%80%99s%20vote.%20Barjora%2C%20Gangajalghati%2C%20Onda%2C%20Bankura%20II%2C%20Bishnupur%2C%20Taldangra%2C%20Kotulpur%2C%20Joypur%2C%20Patrasayar%2C%20Indas%20and%20Sonamukhi%20blocks%20and%20Bishnupur%20and%20Sonamukhi%20municipalities%20make%20up%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202021%20assembly%20election%2C%20the%20cumulative%20vote%20share%20in%20the%20seven%20seats%20concerned%20was%206%2C77%2C147%20votes%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%206%2C48%2C438%20votes%20for%20the%20TMC%20and%201%2C25%2C686%20votes%20for%20the%20Left-Congress%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Ranaghat%20Lok%20Sabha%20of%20Nadia%20district%20in%20central%20Bengal%2C%20the%20local%20body%20election%20results%20put%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20votes%20at%207%2C05%2C022%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20at%204%2C24%2C538%20and%20the%20Left-Congress%E2%80%99%20at%202%2C02%2C912.%20Nabadwip%2C%20Santipur%2C%20Ranaghat%20I%20and%20II%2C%20Hanskhali%2C%20Chakdah%20and%20Krishnaganj%20blocks%20and%20Ranaghat%2C%20Birnagar%2C%20Santipur%2C%20Nabadwip%20an