%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20late%2019th%20century%2C%20when%20the%20Mughal%20emperors%20were%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20Malwa%20region%20of%20the%20state.%20During%20an%20unscheduled%20halt%2C%20they%20suddenly%20felt%20the%20craving%20to%20consume%20%3Cem%3Esevaiyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20creamy%20pudding%20dessert%20consumed%20during%20Eid%20is%20primarily%20made%20with%20wheat%2C%20a%20crop%20that%20was%20unavailable%20in%20the%20royal%20camp%20of%20Ratlam%20during%20the%20period.%20Desperate%20to%20satiate%20the%20craving%2C%20the%20Mughals%20requested%20the%20local%20tribal%20community%20of%20Bhil%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Esevaiyan%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20the%20locally%20available%20gram%20flour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20voila!%20This%20is%20what%20led%20to%20the%20first%20recipe%20of%20Ratlami%20sev.%20Originally%2C%20the%20name%20given%20to%20the%20vermicelli%20was%20Bhildi%20Sev%2C%20after%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Bhil%20tribe%2C%20who%20are%20credited%20as%20the%20snack%E2%80%99s%20original%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fratlam-sev-1688647361.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Formerly%20known%20as%20Ratnapuri%2C%20Ratlam%20was%20created%20by%20Raja%20Ratan%20Singh%20Rathore%20%E2%80%94%20the%20great-grandson%20of%20Raja%20Udai%20Singh%20of%20Jodhpur%20%E2%80%94%20in%201652.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fratlam-sev-1688647361.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fratlam-sev-1688647361-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fratlam-sev-1688647361-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fratlam-sev-1688647361-768x402.jpg%207